# work-nc-whmcs — General Rules

## Stack
- Platform: WHMCS server module (PHP)
- Remote: Nextcloud SaaS Manager `manage.sh` v11.x via SSH (phpseclib3)
- Database: MariaDB/MySQL (WHMCS native — no module migrations)
- Tests: PHPUnit 10.5 in `tests/` (isolated vendor)
- CI: GitHub Actions `validation-gate` (php-whmcs stack)

## Language and style
- Code: English (variables, functions, comments)
- User communication: Brazilian Portuguese
- Commits: Conventional Commits in English (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `test:`)

## Principles
- Minimize diff scope — WHMCS module callbacks are global functions; do not rename `nextcloudsaas_*`
- Functions max ~30 lines; extract helpers in `lib/` when needed
- Errors explicit — never empty catch; log via `Helper::log()` for module diagnostics
- Security: never log passwords; HaRP shared key admin-only (v3.1.7+)

## WHMCS constraints
- Deploy paths: `modules/servers/nextcloudsaas/` + `includes/hooks/nextcloudsaas_hooks.php`
- Domain resolution: always use `Helper::getDomain()` — never assume `$params['domain']` alone
- Idempotent `CreateAccount`: check `SSHManager::instanceExists()` before `manage.sh create`

## PMO
- Present a brief plan before coding multi-file changes
- Ask before modifying more than 5 files in one task
- Never remove code without explaining why
